## Complete Agent Reference (all 31)

⚡ = required gate (auto-runs without user confirmation when triggered)

### ASK stage — Frame the question

| Agent | When to use | What it does |
|-------|-------------|-------------|
| problem-framer | Problem statement is vague or lacks a metric | Turns fuzzy business concerns into a crisp analytical question with a named decision |
| metric-translator | "Success criteria" lacks a formula or baseline | Converts ambiguous goals (e.g., "improve retention") into measurable KPIs with numerator/denominator |
| hypothesis-gen | Hypothesis Tree is empty | Builds a MECE 4-branch tree (Product / Audience / External / Data) with effort ratings |
| scope-guard ⚡ | Scope section empty or multiple questions bundled | Enforces single-question focus, splits bundled questions, adds rabbit hole guard |

### LOOK stage — Understand the data

| Agent | When to use | What it does |
|-------|-------------|-------------|
| data-scout | Data Sources section empty | Maps every hypothesis to a specific table, flags unmapped hypotheses with cheapest alternative |
| tracking-auditor | Event or log data is the primary source | Audits 5 dimensions: schema, version drift, deduplication, coverage gaps, definition alignment |
| lineage-mapper | Same metric appears in multiple tools or layers | Traces raw → mart → BI tool, detects definition conflicts, enforces single source of truth |
| sampling-designer | Sampling section empty or comparison groups undefined | Defines unit of analysis, checks survivorship bias, calculates required sample size |
| sql-writer | Data sources confirmed but no queries in assets/ | Generates one SQL template per hypothesis with "Signal if TRUE / FALSE" comments |
| data-quality-sentinel ⚡ | LOOK→INVESTIGATE transition or quality flags | Audits 7 dimensions including Simpson's paradox and survivorship bias; issues Go/No-Go |

### INVESTIGATE stage — Test hypotheses

| Agent | When to use | What it does |
|-------|-------------|-------------|
| eda-agent | Results section empty before hypothesis testing | Produces a context-specific EDA plan oriented to ruling out hypotheses, with stop criteria |
| experiment-designer | A/B test or causal claim detected | Designs experiment with traffic check, SRM detection, guardrails, and stopping rules |
| causal-agent | Causal claim present but no experiment | Selects quasi-experimental method, tests identifying assumption, scopes honest conclusions |
| root-cause-analyst | Multiple open hypotheses in scorecard | Builds root cause tree with contribution estimates, verification roadmap, and stopping criteria |
| anomaly-detector | Spike or anomaly detected in Initial Observations | Classifies anomaly type, runs isolation tests, prioritizes data artifact check first |
| stats-agent | Hypothesis scorecard has results needing validation | Selects correct statistical test, applies multiple testing correction, translates effect size to business terms |
| ml-agent | Analysis type is Modeling (📈) | Designs full ML pipeline: leakage audit, validation strategy, fairness trigger, deployment pattern |
| forecast-agent | Time-series forecasting needed | Checks history sufficiency, selects method, maps prediction intervals to operational thresholds |
| peer-reviewer | Results or findings have substantive content | Scores 5 dimensions, cites exact text for every issue, enforces MECE check for INVESTIGATE |
| reproducibility-keeper ⚡ | Reproducibility section empty at INVESTIGATE→EVOLVE | Packages queries, snapshots, environment, and step-by-step reproduction instructions |

### VOICE stage — Communicate findings

| Agent | When to use | What it does |
|-------|-------------|-------------|
| chart-recommender | Findings present but no visualization guidance | Matches data structure to chart type, enforces finding-as-title rule, matches tool to config |
| dashboard-designer | Multiple layered metrics need ongoing monitoring | Designs KPI tree dashboard with drill-down logic and alert definitions sourced from config |
| narrative-agent | Audience-specific Messages section empty | Crafts stakeholder-specific messages with quantified impact, one ask, and anticipated objection |
| exec-summarizer | Executive Summary is empty or generic | Produces 1-page summary: impact → finding → recommendation → risk → decision requested |
| decision-memo-writer | Recommendation ready to formalize | Creates decision document with "We will NOT" alternatives, success criteria, and review triggers |
| peer-reviewer | Findings have content ready for external review | Reviews VOICE stage: So What quantification, Now What concreteness, limitations prominence |

### EVOLVE stage — Institutionalize learning

| Agent | When to use | What it does |
|-------|-------------|-------------|
| metric-definer | New metric proposed in analysis | Formalizes with STEDII framework: formula, edge cases, counter-metric, config.md entry |
| semantic-layer-engineer | Metric finalized and needs to be standardized | Generates dbt/LookML/Cube definition with breaking change assessment and rollout plan |
| dre-agent | Monitoring Setup section empty | Designs SLO, alert routing, regression safeguard, and investigation runbook with specific SQL |
| data-product-manager | Reusable dataset or metric created | Plans data product: contract, SLA, adoption tracking, roadmap, and deprecation trigger |
| governance-steward | New metric or terminology introduced | Updates GLOSSARY.md, assigns named owners, defines access control, sets change management |
| reproducibility-keeper ⚡ | EVOLVE transition | Verifies full reproducibility package before archiving |

### CROSS-stage (any)

| Agent | When to use | What it does |
|-------|-------------|-------------|
| ethics-guard ⚡ | PII keywords detected or Modeling fairness trigger | Audits PII (including quasi-identifiers), analytical bias, and compliance (GDPR/PIPA/HIPAA) |

